title: Hobi jealous angst request Part 1
body:
Ya’ll know the drill, we gotta do this jealous angst part before we get to the smut with all seven boys but I’m telling you it HURT me to hurt Hobi

Anonymous asked: Hello idk if you would like to do this but I was wondering if you could do a reaction to bts getting jealous over a guy hitting on their female best friend or crush, they argue bad and then after a week of not talking or arguing and sexual ten everything explodes in a hot mess of jealousy sex. Like carnal rough sex! Pls and thank you!

Warnings: angst, a little seductive possessiveness,  touching without explicitly asking permission

Word Count: 703

Hobi has been psyching himself up for days to ask you out.

You’ve been friends with everyone for a few months but you and Hobi were partners in crime, laughing together, getting into trouble at parties pranking Namjoon and Jungkook, him driving you around at 3am to find a very specific dark chocolate because neither of you could sleep.

Hobi has been seeing sunshine in your eyes for weeks, and he doesn’t even know why he’s so nervous. You’re just so open and bright and he’s worried that if you were interested you would’ve said so already.

He’s scoping out restaurants to take you to when he sees you inside a local Italian place with your hand on some guy’s arm, and he stops dead in his tracks, looking through the plate glass.

Please don’t let this be a date, please don’t let this be a date, he’s saying it over and over in his mind and he feels like his heart might burst from how hard it’s beating when he watches, ducked down in the front seat of his car, when you bid him goodnight.

He looks away when the guy leans down to kiss you, and waits for you to get in your car and leave before he goes into the restaurant and orders a shot.

You’re shocked when there’s a knock at your door past midnight, and you answer it in sleeping shorts and a camisole, breathing a sigh of relief when it’s your best friend, all glassy eyed, leaning against your doorjamb.

“Hoseok! You scared me!” You say with a laugh, opening the door wide to let him in. “Why didn’t you invite me to the party?”

He shrugs and doesn’t make a move to come in.

“Thought you might be busy.”

“Busy? Why? Come in and stop leaning against the doorjamb like a rebel without a cause.”

You’re teasing him but God, he does look good, leather jacket, white t-shirt contrasting with that golden skin of his, black hair swept back with locks falling into his face.

He comes in, finally, and he’s more drunk than you thought because you can smell the liquor on him. He’s avoiding your eyes.

“Is…is everything okay?”

He looks at you and there’s something in his eyes you can’t put your finger on, jaw clenched tight.

“So you had a date, yeah?”

You startle. “A date?”

“Don’t fucking lie to me,” he says, almost growling, and it sends a chill of pleasure down your spine.

He’d never been angry with you like this and you couldn’t believe how hot it was making you.

“I…I wasn’t! Yeah, I had a date.”

He steps closer to you, and you back up until your ass hits the kitchen counter.

He takes your chin in his hand, looking at your mouth.

“He got to kiss these lips before I did. Did he get to touch you, too?”

He skates a hand down your body, from your collarbone to your hip, and you’re quaking inside.

“Hoseok…”

He works a thigh between your legs and you spread them instinctively, your heart racing at how close his face is to yours and how much you want him to kiss you.

“Don’t say my name like that, Y/n..I’ve wanted you for so long.”

“Hoseok,” you say, again, almost defiantly, and he groans and crushes his mouth to yours, grabbing the back of your head.

You melt under him and he’s got one hand sliding under the waistband of your shorts and you’re bucking your hips when he breaks the kiss and takes a step back, breathing hard.

“I’m sorry,” he says hoarsely. “I’m sorry. I’m drunk and I’ve been feeling crazy all night, ever since I saw you with him.”

Your mouth is dry, mind racing. “Saw me? Hobi, what-”

“Ignore this. Ignore me. Too many shots at the bar, that’s all.”

He gives you a tight smile and you put your hand on his face.

“Hey…tell me what is going on with you.”

He turns his face into your hand, only for a second, and then smiles again, more warmly.

“Everything’s fine. I’ll call you tomorrow, yeah?”

He’s opening the door and leaving before your head can stop spinning.

Anonymous asked: Hello idk if you would like to do this but I was wondering if you could do a reaction to bts getting jealous over a guy hitting on their female best friend or crush, they argue bad and then after a week of not talking or arguing and sexual ten everything explodes in a hot mess of jealousy sex. Like carnal rough sex! Pls and thank you!

Warnings: angst, a little seductive possessiveness,  touching without explicitly asking permission

Word Count: 703

Hobi has been psyching himself up for days to ask you out.

You’ve been friends with everyone for a few months but you and Hobi were partners in crime, laughing together, getting into trouble at parties pranking Namjoon and Jungkook, him driving you around at 3am to find a very specific dark chocolate because neither of you could sleep.

Hobi has been seeing sunshine in your eyes for weeks, and he doesn’t even know why he’s so nervous. You’re just so open and bright and he’s worried that if you were interested you would’ve said so already.

He’s scoping out restaurants to take you to when he sees you inside a local Italian place with your hand on some guy’s arm, and he stops dead in his tracks, looking through the plate glass.

Please don’t let this be a date, please don’t let this be a date, he’s saying it over and over in his mind and he feels like his heart might burst from how hard it’s beating when he watches, ducked down in the front seat of his car, when you bid him goodnight.

He looks away when the guy leans down to kiss you, and waits for you to get in your car and leave before he goes into the restaurant and orders a shot.

You’re shocked when there’s a knock at your door past midnight, and you answer it in sleeping shorts and a camisole, breathing a sigh of relief when it’s your best friend, all glassy eyed, leaning against your doorjamb.

“Hoseok! You scared me!” You say with a laugh, opening the door wide to let him in. “Why didn’t you invite me to the party?”

He shrugs and doesn’t make a move to come in.

“Thought you might be busy.”

“Busy? Why? Come in and stop leaning against the doorjamb like a rebel without a cause.”

You’re teasing him but God, he does look good, leather jacket, white t-shirt contrasting with that golden skin of his, black hair swept back with locks falling into his face.

He comes in, finally, and he’s more drunk than you thought because you can smell the liquor on him. He’s avoiding your eyes.

“Is…is everything okay?”

He looks at you and there’s something in his eyes you can’t put your finger on, jaw clenched tight.

“So you had a date, yeah?”

You startle. “A date?”

“Don’t fucking lie to me,” he says, almost growling, and it sends a chill of pleasure down your spine.

He’d never been angry with you like this and you couldn’t believe how hot it was making you.

“I…I wasn’t! Yeah, I had a date.”

He steps closer to you, and you back up until your ass hits the kitchen counter.

He takes your chin in his hand, looking at your mouth.

“He got to kiss these lips before I did. Did he get to touch you, too?”

He skates a hand down your body, from your collarbone to your hip, and you’re quaking inside.

“Hoseok…”

He works a thigh between your legs and you spread them instinctively, your heart racing at how close his face is to yours and how much you want him to kiss you.

“Don’t say my name like that, Y/n..I’ve wanted you for so long.”

“Hoseok,” you say, again, almost defiantly, and he groans and crushes his mouth to yours, grabbing the back of your head.

You melt under him and he’s got one hand sliding under the waistband of your shorts and you’re bucking your hips when he breaks the kiss and takes a step back, breathing hard.

“I’m sorry,” he says hoarsely. “I’m sorry. I’m drunk and I’ve been feeling crazy all night, ever since I saw you with him.”

Your mouth is dry, mind racing. “Saw me? Hobi, what-”

“Ignore this. Ignore me. Too many shots at the bar, that’s all.”

He gives you a tight smile and you put your hand on his face.

“Hey…tell me what is going on with you.”

He turns his face into your hand, only for a second, and then smiles again, more warmly.

“Everything’s fine. I’ll call you tomorrow, yeah?”

He’s opening the door and leaving before your head can stop spinning.

summary: Never, not once, have I been moved to tears at a concert the way BTS moved me. I've never felt that love, that passion, that...
body:
Never, not once, have I been moved to tears at a concert the way BTS moved me. I’ve never felt that love, that passion, that pure joy that I felt these past two nights at the Rose Bowl. The love these 7 men have for what they’re doing, for ARMY, is unreal. You can hear it in their voice and see it in their eyes.

I’ve been to a lot of concerts for groups I have loved, and still do love. Until this weekend I hadn’t ever felt that love back, and it was humbling. BTS deserves everything they have and more.

body:
Yoongi - D1

“This is not a date” you say for the third time today.

You’re watching your boyfriend look over sound equipment and you try to understand his excitement, butusic production doesnt really scream out at you. You adjust your own face mask and glasses as one of bighit makeup artist stand in front of you to cover any interaction with Yoongi.

“This is only sold in LA, y/n” he says lowering his face mask, not looking at you.

Usually a date consist of face masks, hidden entrances, black cars, and as little sunlight as possible. So when he asked you to go out with him this morning - you did not expect to drive to a music shop with two body gaurds, two makeup aritist, and hoseok. This was both a safety and privacy protocol for both of you.

You couldn’t be seen out alone together in broad daylight so this was the only way, hence this is not a date.

“I am also only sold in America, so you’re basically choosing that over me” you tease.

“It does seem to have more features…” you hold back a laugh. “Kidding”

“Can I get this?” You point at a portable speaker, but before you can say kidding one of his assistance already takes it to check out for you. “Um…”

“It’s my gift to you for all of this” Yoongi clarifies coming up to you directly to talk. Security guard already on the move to block any visibility from the rest of the world.

“You really know what a girl wants”

“I did rent out a therater for us and the boys so-“

“You did not!” You joke “stop flexing on all of us broke individual”

“Flexing” he laughs at your words and nods slightly coming as close as he’s allowed to, “so should I tell you now or later about the soundproff walls I had installed?”

“Why do you think those walls are for me?” You shrug knowing fully well you’re going to need them tonight

His eyes crinkle to show he’s laughing under his mask.

A/n ~ masterlist is on my homepage
